Alongside this economic weaponization, the administration moved to expand and normalize emergency powers. Trump declared a formal \'93armed conflict\'94 with drug cartels, labeling them terrorist organizations and treating drug trafficking as a war rather than a crime. This framing opened the door to military strikes in Venezuela and to treating suspected smugglers as \'93unlawful combatants,\'94 with fewer legal protections. At the same time, he told reporters that the shutdown would be used to make \'93irreversible\'94 cuts to social programs. In both domains, the language of crisis\'97war abroad, fiscal emergency at home\'97was used to justify actions that would once have required broad debate and clear legal authority.\
