The military itself was drawn deeper into domestic politics. Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth summoned hundreds of generals and admirals to Quantico for an unprecedented meeting on \'93warrior ethos,\'94 and Trump announced he would attend. In speeches there and in related events, Hegseth and Trump did more than talk about readiness. Hegseth rolled back rules of engagement designed to protect civilians, weakened whistleblower protections, and attacked diversity and environmental initiatives as distractions. Trump told the assembled officers that domestic unrest was an \'93invasion from within,\'94 suggested using cities like San Francisco and New York as training grounds, and warned that commanders who did not follow his directives could be dismissed. The message was simple. Loyalty to the president would be the measure of a good officer.\
