\
Against this backdrop, the civil service itself became both target and terrain. The deferred resignation program and planned mass firings shrank the workforce. The firing of acting US attorney Michele Beckwith, hours after she reminded Border Patrol to obey a federal court order, showed that insisting on legality could cost a career. FBI Director Kash Patel dismissed a trainee for displaying a Pride flag, calling it \'93political signage,\'94 despite the employee\'92s record as a diversity coordinator. Defense Secretary Hegseth moved to overhaul the Pentagon\'92s inspector general office while under investigation, and the Pentagon planned to require thousands of staff to sign nondisclosure agreements and undergo random polygraphs to hunt leakers. Whistleblowers and watchdogs were not just unprotected. They were being actively discouraged.\
