Looking ahead from Week 37, several processes were already in motion. Courts were set to hear arguments on Oregon\'92s challenge to the Portland troop deployment and on the legality of the administration\'92s immigration rules that tied victim services to immigration status. The Supreme Court scheduled full arguments on Trump\'92s attempt to remove Federal Reserve Governor Lisa Cook for January, a case that would test the boundary between presidential will and institutional independence. The emergency stay in the TPS case signaled that the Court would also shape the fate of tens of thousands of Venezuelan and Haitian residents. In Congress, hearings were planned on the FCC chair\'92s role in pressuring broadcasters over a late-night show, and on the broader conduct of the shutdown. None of these were speculative. They were already on the calendar, and their outcomes would either reinforce or restrain the trends visible this week.\
